        "id": 1000000
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T10:08:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Who is anticipated to consume those?  We don\u0027t do diagnostics through parsing journal logs.  Is this just for manufacturing?\n\nWhich of these parts are already represented by EEPROMs?  If they have an EEPROM we don\u0027t also need a GPIO-based presence detect.\n\nIf these parts don\u0027t have an EEPROM, but they are possibly removable, why don\u0027t we have an inventory object for them?",
      "parentUuid": "421c52bb_306bbc06",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 15,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "c3c54228a677e458f7e7cf9bfc564da79e7d0b9d",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0709c9a3_7a366521",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002850
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T11:01:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The intent was not to use journal log parsing as a diagnostics mechanism.\n\nThis requirement came from the DFT team to provide visibility for removable device present/absent transitions. EEPROM-backed devices can create inventory objects, but hot-removal may not immediately provide a clear removal transition to the user. The GPIODeviceDetect entries were added to expose present/absent transitions through the existing gpio-presence flow.\n\nAnother option is to use the GPIO transition to trigger FruDeviceManager.ReScanBus for the affected FRU bus, so EEPROM-backed inventory is refreshed when the removable device state changes. I can rework the change in that direction if preferred.",
      "parentUuid": "b1907af1_5d7d05b1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 15,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "c3c54228a677e458f7e7cf9bfc564da79e7d0b9d",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
